-- U.S. Stock Futures Decline as Data Bolsters Case for QE Tapering
-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 2013-07-31T12:36:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-31/u-s-stock-futures-decline-as-data-bolsters-case-for-qe-tapering.html
U.S. stock futures retreated as
reports showed faster-than-forecast growth in the economy and
private payrolls, spurring concern the  Federal Reserve  will
begin reducing monetary stimulus this year.  Futures on the Standard & Poorâ€™s 500 Index expiring in
September slipped 0.1 percent to 1,683.2 at 8:35 a.m. in  New
York   Gross domestic product, the value of all goods and services
produced, rose at a 1.7 percent annualized rate, after a 1.1
percent gain the prior quarter, Commerce Department figures
showed today in Washington. The median forecast of 85 economists
surveyed by Bloomberg called for a 1 percent advance for last
quarter.  Consumer spending , the biggest part of the economy,
climbed 1.8 percent after increasing 2.3 percent.  The 200,000 increase in private jobs was more than
projected and followed a revised 198,000 gain in June that was
higher than initially estimated, according to data today from
the ADP Research Institute in Roseland,  New Jersey . The median
forecast of 40 economists surveyed by Bloomberg called for a
July advance of 180,000.  The  S&P 500  has climbed 5 percent this month, its biggest
advance since January, as companies from Apple Inc. to Visa Inc.
reported better-than-estimated earnings. The gauge fell 1.5
percent in June, after seven straight months of gains.  Investors are waiting for guidance from the Federal Reserve
on when it will begin reducing bond purchases and what form
further stimulus will take. The central bank has indicated its
$85 billion monthly bond buying could be trimmed should the
